  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_2' aria-label=\" Dileep Kumar Pandey versus Union of India & Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('2','2025','2025_5_1146_1178','2025INSC749'); ><font size='4'> <strong>DILEEP KUMAR PANDEY<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>UNION OF INDIA & ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 5 S.C.R. 1146</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 749</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010005842025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : ABHAY S. OKA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, AHSANUDDIN AMANULLAH, AUGUSTINE GEORGE MASIH</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether the Air Force School, Bamrauli, in District Allahabad, is a &lsquo;state or authority&rsquo; within the meaning of Art.12 of the Constitution of India; whether it would be amenable to writ jurisdiction u/Art.226 of the Constitution &ndash; Arts.12, 226 &ndash; Writ petitions filed by the appellants-teachers alleging wrong-doings w.r.t actions taken against them by the respondent-Air Force School &ndash; Division Bench of the High Court held that the said School is not a &lsquo;State&rsquo; within the meaning of Art.12<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 21-05-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 10899/2013</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Dismissed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 3 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('2','2025','2025_5_1146_1178','2025INSC749','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='